hot water you actually use you might not even notice the loss in capacity if you notice the reduction in hot water capacity or anticipate that it will be noticeable you can increase the tank temperature from the factory setting of ° degrees to offset the loss in capacity in most installations scalding risk higher temperatures increase the risk of scalding even at °f hot water can scald if you choose a higher temperature setting or to reduce the risk of scaling at any setting install thermostatic mixing valves temperature limiting valves at each pointofuse these valves automatically mix hot and cold water to limit the temperature at the tap when you purchase your water heater the manual will have additional important information regarding water temperature ok i understand the risks ao smith  a o smith all rights reserved a o smith reserves the right to make product changes or improvements at any time without notice rss youtube linkedin twitter facebook water heaters residential gas  propane electric hybrid tankless solar tanks and accessories commercial water heaters boilers storage tanks packaged systems accessories parts waterheaterpartscom parts cross reference service customer support warranty service provider enrollment find a service provider technical training national accounts resources product registration product selector tool naeca guidelines product cross reference product support icomm™ elite remote monitoring contractor rewards warranty prosize™ sizing program logo merchandise technical training advertising tools energy star® products energy guide dsireusaorg product literature spec sheets parts lists instruction manuals piping diagrams revit models wiring diagrams sizing diagrams kit instructions technical bulletins misc technical data warranty sheets brochures catalogs about us about a o smith global facilities contact us newsroom awards and recognition sponsorships case studies careers where to buy for your home or business trade professionals nation